widespread among educated Romans, The Stoic philosophy, which was gaining popularity‚ asserted that the souls of the good would live at least for a considerable period after death. Cicero—at any rate in his later life—identified himself with the New Academy, which affirmed a strong saith in the immortality of the soul.
